text: I love our generation with everyone
using the internet and social media it's
never been easier to meet people I'm a
people person I love meeting others
hearing their stories learning about
their culture and sharing experiences
with them over the last few years I've
been fortunate enough to make friends
all over the world through social media
this is the most rewarding part about my
job hanging out with locals in any given
city is the best way to get the full
experience think about it they know all
the ins and outs just like you do in
your hometown over the last five days in
Morocco I was hosted by two incredible
people Todd and Haddad at their family's
houses they both reached out to me on
snapchat after I said I was coming to
Morocco colleges for me was a simple
response back Saud drove three hours
from his house to pick me up from the
airport in Marrakech where he guided me
around for 24 hours and then drove me
back to his home city of El jedidah his
family gave me a warm welcoming into
their house cooked me a huge meal of
couscous and then Saad took me around
al-jazeera to explore the city and go
jet skiing on the beach the next morning
I hopped on the train to Casablanca
where I was greeted by a Giada and her
brother Omar at the train station they
drove me to their amazing house which
felt more like a Moroccan Palace where I
had my own private guest house their
family could be a huge meal and the next
morning Hassan and Omar gave me a
wonderful tour around Casablanca we
walked around the old city of caboose
hiked up the lighthouse chilled at the
beach ate Moroccan sandwiches and
visited the giant mosque I spent another
night over at their house and I enjoyed
every minute we spent together now as I
sit here on my last day in Morocco
reminiscing on the past few days I have
two new friends and two Moroccan
families to come back to visit my wallet
is full of Moroccan dirham that I went
through at the airport because Saud and
a job didn't let me spend any of my own
money I've said it before and I'll say
it again I've
had better hospitality than in Arabic
countries I'm drew pinsky and if you
like my travel videos please click
Subscribe and join me as I plan to visit
every country in the world
